.TH "free_tx_desc" 9 "free_tx_desc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
free_tx_desc \- reclaims Tx descriptors and their buffers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" free_tx_desc
.BI "(struct adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "struct sge_txq *q "  ","
.BI "unsigned int n "  ","
.BI "bool unmap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
the adapter
.IP "q" 12
the Tx queue to reclaim descriptors from
.IP "n" 12
the number of descriptors to reclaim
.IP "unmap" 12
whether the buffers should be unmapped for DMA

Reclaims Tx descriptors from an SGE Tx queue and frees the associated
Tx buffers.  Called with the Tx queue lock held.
